.TH GIT-REPO-STATE 1 "2026-06-14" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-repo-state \- report repository workflow state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git repo-state
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git repo-state
prints a read-only repository state report: current branch, inferred default
branch, upstream divergence, dirty worktree counts, active operation, stash
count, and current branch pull request details when GitHub data is available.
.PP
The command does not require GitHub access. If
.B gh
is unavailable or unauthenticated, local repository state is still reported and
pull request fields are left empty.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-porcelain
Print stable
.B key=value
output for scripts.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Print a flat JSON object.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
State printed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-checks (1),
.BR git-cleanup-repo (1)
